<font color="#FF0000">THE WINDS OF CHANGE</font><br>
<tt>Sat Aug  9 23:18:26 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Doc,<br><br>
Without knowing you have used the tactics of a true Warrior.  I hope such an act does not tarnish your hard earned reputation.<br><br>
Those who desire to become great Warriors know that real heroes have both brain and brawn.  Only the shrewdest of foe realize that a Warrior will always use his brain before engaging his brawn.  Making allies of your foes is better than fighting them, and diplomacy is better than war.<br><br>
While a draw is better than a loss, the real Warrior will go for the victory.  Winning without having to fight is the sweetest victory of all.  Warriors are never lost to an enemy subdued through diplomacy.<br><br>
The caution we must take is to beware of a zealot.  Zealots are led by their own needs even when the result may be annihilation.<br><br>
As for now you have handed us a sweet victory, and may have found a type of personal victory of your own.<br><br>
I prefer to walk the path taken by my brothers.  We must not attempt to change what cannot be changed because it a terrible waste of energy.  Distinguishing what can from what  cannot be changed is fundamental to a Warriors success.<br><br>
For this reason my brothers are likely to ignore you until you prove you are truely worthy of their wisdom.
<p><code>--   (No name, a silent Warrior) </code><p>


